Titolo: Orc Attack

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Orc Attack is a fixed shooter video game written by Dean Lock for the Atari 8-bit family and published in 1983 by Thorn EMI. The game was re-released, along with Commodore 64 and ZX Spectrum ports, when Thorn rebranded as Creative Sparks, and later at budget price by Sparklers and Top Ten. In Orc Attack, the player protects a castle wall by dropping boulders on ladder climbing orcs. Though the visuals are low resolution, Orc Attack has a high level of violence.